snippet.title: Dyson AM06
snippet.description: The AM06 is an impressive spectacle to behold -- but it's still just a desk fan. For such an expensive device, we wish that it doubled as a space heater, like Dyson's AM05, or featured a more noticeable bump in performance. It doesn't, and that makes it difficult to recommend.

snippet.title: Lenovo ThinkPad X1 Carbon
snippet.description: The third version of Lenovo's ultralight 14-inch laptop, the X1 Carbon, gets nearly all the basics right while adding a few new twists, including a function key row that changes app by app.

snippet.title: Lenovo ThinkPad Yoga
snippet.description: Lenovo solves half the Yoga equation with a clever hidden keyboard on the ThinkPad Yoga. If we could combine this with the higher-res screen and better looks of the consumer version, we'd have the ultimate hybrid.

snippet.title: ThinkPad T43 - First Take
snippet.description: The IBM ThinkPad T43 delivers similar performance to but lesser battery life than the identically designed ThinkPad T42; we think the latter remains the better buy.

snippet.title: Fan TV
snippet.description: Fan TV is the latest box promises to unify cable TV, streaming video and movies, but it faces an uphill battle to get cable companies on board.

snippet.title: Lenovo ThinkPad 11e
snippet.description: Students get four 11-inch choices, Windows or Chrome OS, in both touch or non-touch.

snippet.title: Lenovo ThinkPad 8
snippet.description: If you’re craving full Windows 8 on a tablet the size of an iPad Mini, and want a great display, the ThinkPad 8 is one of the best we’ve seen...but not by much.

snippet.title: Dead Space 3 (Xbox 360)
snippet.description: Action-packed and suspenseful, Dead Space 3 impresses, even if it's a lot of the same.

snippet.title: Lenovo ThinkPad X1 Carbon Touch
snippet.description: The business-oriented Lenovo ThinkPad X1 adds must-have features for 2013, and remains a very impressive business-oriented ultrabook with strong crossover appeal.

snippet.title: Lenovo ThinkPad X1
snippet.description: The business-oriented Lenovo ThinkPad X1 has a few quirks, but is otherwise a very impressive business-oriented ultrabook with strong crossover potential.
